SIMPLE: exertion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exertion
<hw>Ex*er"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
exerting, or putting into motion or action; the active exercise of any
power or faculty; an effort, esp. a laborious or perceptible effort;
<as>as, an <ex>exertion</ex> of strength or power; an <ex>exertion</ex>
of the limbs or of the mind; it is an <ex>exertion</ex> for him to move,
to-day</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Attempt; endeavor; effort; essay; trial. See
<er>Attempt</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exertive</ent>⟦br⟧
